data.name: EukMetaSanity
data.description: Structural and functional annotation of eukaryotic metagenome-assembled genomes

evidence: README indicates network usage: "EukMetaSanity is built using the [YAPIM](https://github.com/cjneely10/YAPIM) library, which operates through a configuration file that is provided with each pipeline."

"Eukaryotic genome annotation is a laborious and time-intensive process. **EukMetaSanity** provides a structural and functional annotation of MAGs in a highly-parallel fashion, allowing for quick and in-depth analyses."

Usage is described via running pipelines with `yapim run ...` on input genomes to produce annotation outputs (GFF3, FASTA, quality reports), indicating it is an end-user analysis application rather than a library.
